* '''Player:''' Lady Servil, I freed your son, but he went to help your husband.
* '''Lady Servil:''' No! Please, you have to help them!
* {{tact|end}}

===Upon killing the Khazard Ogre===
* '''General Khazard:''' Well, well, well, you seem to be in quite the rush. Do you have somewhere else to be?
* '''Sammy Servil:''' Oh no...
* '''Player:''' General Khazard, I presume?
* '''General Khazard:''' You presume correct. I must say, I sense a great air of defiance to you. Does my appearance not fill you with fear?
* '''Player:''' I've seen worse.
* '''General Khazard:''' How arrogant. No matter though, you will come to learn.
* '''General Khazard:''' Now, despite your entertaining show, the two individuals you are attempting to leave with are my property.
* '''Player:''' They belong to nobody!
* '''General Khazard:''' Ha! Well if their freedom is so valuable to you, how about a trade? Fight in my arena, and if you win, I'll let them go.
* '''Player:''' And what if I refuse your offer?
* '''General Khazard:''' Well... I wasn't actually giving you a choice. Guards, take [him/her/them] to the cells.
* {{qact|The player is taken to a jail cell.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to a spectator after defeating the ogre===
